reviewText: Wanda has always been a favorite comedian of mine and this is a fabulous example why.  I laughed so hard I was constantly crying.  Very enjoyable.  What a natural gift.
summary: Laughed so hard I was crying
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: You tell em' Wanda! Those pesky republicans simply can't stand President Obama being the Commander in Chief! The best parts are when she talkes about Michelle and Barack Obama living in the White House, what to say or not to say at her first correspondents dinner, the pirates off the coast of Africa and her own experiences with hair waxing!Wanda is simply crazy funny and one great story teller.  So down to earth, so real, so right on.I can't wait for her next video, on the re-election of Obama. So much material for her to draw from.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: I CAN NOT STOP LAUGHING WHEN I WATCH HER COMEDY SHOW ON STAGE. IF YOU DO NOT HAVE THIS ONE, YOU NEED TO ORDER IT.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: This is one of the funniest shows I've seen. Being from the old school( Red Foxx-Richard Pryor-Moms Mabley ) I laughed so hard, I almost cried uh-huh. I recommend this DVD to all my old school friends In Chicago, L A and Arizona.Gran Gran.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: This is one of her best shows.  Watching the audience get such a thrill out of her routines made it even funnier.  She tackles any subject and makes it hilarious, from President Obama to having children, and so on.  She can find humor in anything, and she takes her audience along for the ride, laughing hysterically all the way.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: If you're looking for something to watch for a night in, this is a great video to get. My only negative comment is that she used a couple of jokes from the Correspondents Dinner. I feel like I shouldn't have to pay for something you just gave me for free, but maybe that's just me. Wanda Sykes is hilarious without having to be excessive like Monique, Adele Givens, etc. I'm still a fan of theirs but they are a bit too much sometimes.Bottom line: If you're already a Wanda Sykes fan, no need to be concerned, just click "buy" right now. If you've never hear her before, this won't be your last time buying her DVD.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: very witty and makes me laugh still after watching it for the 11th time. Glad i purchased it and it was shipped to me quickly!
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: I miss the old Wanda...this one is too political.  Most of it is about politics and gay marriage...I expected more (although the Ester Roll part was hilarious!).  I do not recommend.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: There's no one like Wanda Sykes. I love her sly bluntness. She's always edgy and always hilarious. This is from 2010, her second HBO comedy special live from Washington D.C. She covers everything from motherhood, aging, coming out as gay and our first black President.Spectacular comedy. Not to be missed.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: Wanda Sykes is just hilarious and constantly keeps you laughing throughout.  This is her second comedy special for HBO done in 2009 and she comments on Barack Obama's presidency, her new life in a interracial lesbian marriage, Bikini waxing and being a performer on a all gay cruise ship with 3,200 couples.  She is amazingly funny, honest and provocatively rough around the edges.  Her ability to entertain is enormous and she is a strong and fearless woman.  Wanda has much strength to admire, sharp wit to enjoy and it all comes out in fearless comedy.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: Wanda Sykes is one of the funniest comedians ever. She covers so many topics and each is funnier than the next. I saw this many times on HBO and laughed more each time I watched it. I had to have it so I could watch it whenever I needed a good laugh. You won't be disappointed!
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: Not many things get me to respond emotionally, but Ms. Sykes had me laughing out loud with her brilliant and candid comentary. Just about all the things that we think about, speak in private about and wonder about was exposed in a very satyrical manner, with facial expressions, and body language that I rearly see in comedy,
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: This is one of Wanda Skyes BEST live performance.  I was laughing so hard I couldn't breath. If you haven't seen this and want a good laugh, then BUY IT.
Title: Wanda Sykes: I'ma Be Me

reviewText: I loved this DVD the most.  Wanda hits every issue for women, gays and politics.  Watched it with friends at home and just about killed us off with hysterical laughter.
